<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-06-05T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-06-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="505" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d505">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">Marshall Mission Files, Lot 54–D270:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">General <persName type="from">Hsu
                                    Yung-chang</persName> to General <persName type="to">Hsiung
                                    Shih-hui</persName>, at Mukden</hi><note n="94" xml:id="d505fn94">Copy transmitted to General Marshall by Brig. Gen.
                                Peter T. K. Pee, personal aide to Generalissimo Chiang
                                Kai-shek.</note></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi></placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-06-05">5 June 1946</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>The Executive Headquarters, Peiping, will establish a branch office in
                            Changchun. Pending further instructions, that office shall then start
                            functioning. In the preparatory period you should render every
                            assistance and convenience to the said office.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>